rComments: Loved the movement(dance breaks). He has a deep knowledge pool and shares a lot of it in class. His website is incredibly organized and filled with excellent notes that help you become a better programmer. His assignments were tough but easily doable if you started more than 3 days before the deadline. Tests were exactly what he said he would test.

The worst prof I have ever meet. He is an intelligent person, but he is not a great proof. I really do not like his style, as well as his assignments are tough and boring. The assignment instruction is damn ambiguous. And he did not tell you any detail or demo of the assignment. You have to guess how should you do based on the compiled code.

On his lecture, He speaks and types so fast, I could rarely follow his step. He provided huge amount of materials which is useful for us to learn, that's good. Assignments took quite plenty of time to learn and think about it. Exams are quite hard to gain scores, though it seems easy.
background knowledge required else all the best
Good prof, seems to really care about teaching. There was lots of resources available if you were struggling. Tests and exam were open book but still tricky, and the assignments were fair.

AJR really cares, and goes above and beyond to help his students. He responds to questions by email quicker and with more depth than any professor I've had. The course covers some challenging material, so stay a bit ahead and you will get a lot more out of the lectures. His course website is an invaluable resource.
He's brilliant; however he has a very droning and monotonous voice that puts me to sleep after an hour of lecture... he does upload notes however, but lectures are KEY to acing the class.
Really good Proff  really got me ready for upper year courses.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Really good prof, although his lectures were a bit boring and hard to pay attention, everything else was good, he made sure he helped everyone, assignments were good made perfect sense, his midterm was also doable, and it was general a good course
really boring prof course website is just huge blocks of text boring prof hard to follow his lectures sleep inducing prof
Terrible notes. Very disorganized. He really knows his stuff but is not so good at delivering his knowledge to students in an engaging manner. Lectures really boring.
His tests are really hard to get high although they seem easy. Pay attention to all kinds of details in C Programming

Very clear and helpful. Course website was an amazing resource. Clearly understands the conditions people in software industry actually work under -- he allowed us to bring any book we wanted into exam as a resource. No unfair difficulty.
